  "text": "With this grading, Sym(U) is a Koszul algebra. Therefore, by a result of Martinez-Villa [CITATION_1] , B = Sym(U)#G is also a Koszul algebra, and its Koszul dual is isomorphic to A = E (U)#G . Here, E (V ) = Sym(V ) ! = k≥0 k U * denotes the exterior algebra on U and we use the natural action of G on E (U), which is given by gf (u) = f (g −1 u) for f ∈ U * and u ∈ U.",
